If you subscribe to The New York Times via Google, payment for your subscription will be automatically charged to your Google Play account upon confirmation. Subscriptions renew automatically 24-hours prior to the start of the next billing period. Billing occurs every calendar month for a monthly subscription or once-yearly for an annual subscription. Subscriptions continue to renew automatically until cancelled. You can manage and cancel subscriptions using the Google Play subscription center.

For offers that include a free trial: If you cancel before the end of the free trial, you will not be charged. After the free trial period, you will automatically become a paying subscriber. If you choose to upgrade or downgrade your subscription during the free trial period, you will forfeit the remainder of the free trial.

Offers not open to current subscribers with the same subscription type. The print edition of The New York Times (Home Delivery) is not included with digital subscriptions. Home Delivery subscriptions include All Digital Access (All Access). New York Times Cooking, Games, Wirecutter and The Athletic are referred to as Standalone subscriptions, and do not include digital or print news. Basic Digital Access subscriptions (Basic Access) do not include Standalone access. All Digital Access subscriptions do include Standalone access.
